Blue-chip stocks zigzagged in a rudderless market  Thursday as bond interest rates held steady.
The Dow Jones index of 30 leading industrials slipped 1.23 point to  3,754.07 at 11:00 a.m. (1500 GMT). Roughly 83 million shares were traded on  the New York Stock Exchange.
On the bond market, interest rates on the main 30-year Treasury bond  averaged 7.34 percent, unchanged from late Wednesday.
Philip Morris stock fell 3.50 dollars to 50.25 dollars. The company  announced Wednesday that it would take no action for the moment on splitting  its tobacco business from its food and beer operations.
Trading on the stock was suspended Wednesday as speculation mounted that  Philip Morris' board of directors would announce the split after its meeting.
